ch.rs.reflectorgrid

Annotation Type TransferGrid


  • @Documented
 @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
 @Target(value=FIELD)
public @interface TransferGrid
    This annotation is supposed to be used in conjunction with ReflectorGrid. It has different variables which are used to set different options during the creation of the grid. the enum Fieldtype is used to define if the Field is constructed using a TextField or TextArea. editable is used to define if a variable is read only or can also be written to. options is used, once filled, to create a comboBox for the variable. This is, in terms of hierarchy, above the fieldtype enum. As soon as you fill something into options, the field for the corresponding variable turns into a ComboBox.
    Author:
    Ricardo Daniel Monteiro Simoes

    • Element Detail

      • editable

        public abstract boolean editable
        This defines if a variable is write and read or read only. default is set to true. true == write/read false == read only
        Returns:
        if it is editable or not
        Default:
        true

      • options

        public abstract String[] options
        This defines if the variable is supposed to be set using a ComboBox. This is above fieldtype. If you give options any input, it will turn into a ComboBox, no matter the setting in fieldtype To set this variable, please make use of a normal String array. Example: TransferGrid(options = {"full", "half", "none"});
        Returns:
        Stringarray of all options.
        Default:
        {}

      • fieldtype

        public abstract TransferGrid.Fieldtype fieldtype
        This defines what kind of TextInputField you want. Default value is set to TEXTFIELD. You can manually change it to TEXTAREA for something like "notes" in your object. WARNING If options() has been filled, whatever you set here gets ignored.
        Returns:
        the fieldType of a field
        Default:
        ch.rs.reflectorgrid.TransferGrid.Fieldtype.TEXT_FIELD
